# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

{{project_name}} is a Gradio application built with Python 3.11. It provides an interactive web UI with tabbed task interfaces and uses LLM workflows powered by `aiweb_common.WorkflowHandler`.

## Commands

```bash
# Setup
make venv && source venv/bin/activate

# Run Gradio app
python gradio_app.py                          # launches on port 7860

# Run with Docker
docker-compose up --build --force-recreate

# Lint & format
make style                                    # runs black, flake8, isort, autopep8

# Tests
pytest                                        # all tests
pytest tests/gradio_tests/                    # handler tests
pytest tests/ -k test_name                    # single test by name

# Clean
make clean
```

## Architecture

**Entry point:** `gradio_app.py` — Gradio Blocks app with tabbed interface, served on `0.0.0.0:7860`.

### Handler Pattern

```
Gradio UI (gradio_app.py)                     ← UI components, event wiring
       ↓
Handler ({{project_name}}/sample_handler.py)  ← business logic, LLM calls
       ↓
Config  ({{project_name}}/config/config.py)   ← paths, settings, constants
```

UI functions are kept thin; handlers do the heavy lifting.

### Key Base Class

Handlers can inherit from `aiweb_common.WorkflowHandler` (from the `llm_utils` package) for LLM-powered workflows. Always search `llm_utils`/`aiweb_common` for existing functionality before writing new code.

### Configuration

- `{{project_name}}/config/config.py` — paths, settings, UI text, constants
- `.kilocode/rules/` — coding standards referenced by all AI agents (see `AGENTS.md`)

## Testing

Tests live in `tests/gradio_tests/`. All LLM calls must be mocked — no real API calls in tests. Test fixtures in `conftest.py` provide test helpers.

## Code Conventions

Rules are defined in `.kilocode/rules/` and apply to all AI agents working in this repo:

- **Python ≥ 3.11** with full type annotations everywhere
- **Formatting:** Black (line length 100), isort (profile=black), flake8, autopep8. Config in `pyproject.toml`
- **Naming:** `snake_case` for modules/functions/variables, `PascalCase` for classes, `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for constants/enums, `_leading_underscore` for private, `*_async` suffix for async functions
- **Docstrings:** Google style on public interfaces
- **Reuse** `aiweb_common` classes/methods; propose additions to `llm_utils` rather than editing it directly
- **Package management:** `uv` preferred; editable install with `pip install -e .`

## Restricted Files

Never read, write, or commit: `.env`, `.env.*`, `.venv/`, `supersecrets.txt`, `credentials.json`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, `secrets/`, or any file in `data/` containing PHI/PII.
